cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV 

This paper proposes a taxonomy for memory networks, which are commonly used in neural networks for various tasks. The paper discusses the differences and commonalities between different types of memory networks and analyzes their relative expressive power. The paper also provides examples of tasks and problems that can be solved using these networks. Given the focus on neural networks and their organization, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper also discusses natural language processing problems, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, since the paper provides examples of image processing tasks, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible sub-category.
